==English==
===Etymology===
OE. [[agu]], [[ague]], OF. agu, French [[aigu]], sharp, OF. fem. ague, LL. (febris) acuta, a sharp, acute fever, fr. Latin acutus sharp.  See [[Acute]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈgju/

===Noun===
# An acute fever. [Obs.] ``Brenning agues.'' --P. Plowman.
# (Medical) An intermittent fever, attended by alternate cold and hot fits.
# The cold fit or rigor of the intermittent fever; as, fever and ague.
# A chill, or state of shaking, as with cold. --Dryden.


===Transitive Verb===
To strike with an ague, or with a cold fit.